* Email Isn't Magic Pixie Dust: Front-End Strategies for Content That Actually Work

Creating emails and landing pages that render consistently across the fragmented landscape of email clients and browsers presents unique front-end challenges often underestimated. 
This session tackles the quirks: navigating table-based layouts vs. modern CSS, strategies for reliable responsive design, wrangling dark mode inconsistencies, ensuring accessibility 
in constrained environments, and optimizing image/asset loading. We'll explore practical techniques, testing tools, and frameworks to help front-end developers build content that 
reaches the audience effectively, regardless of their device or client.
